  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will help 150 families in the Gongshan Village of Turpan Prefecture of Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region to be self-reliant through Heifer&#x2019;s Values-Based Holistic Community Development (VBHCD) model. All the self-help group members will improve family income through the sustainable livestock development. Project participants will receive two dairy or beef cattle, grass seeds and other related materials in order to produce food and generate income. The Simplified Drip Irrigation System (SDIS) technique will be taught to the participants to encourage ecologically-sound utilization of water resources.  Another 150 families will benefit from &#x201C;passing on the gift&#x201D; of livestock, SDIS materials and other related resources among self-help groups.</narrative>
  </description>
